1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:37,920
=Episode 3=

3
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:41,680
(Year 2012)

4
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:34,439
Feng!

5
00:04:13,510 --> 00:04:15,310
(Yu Ming)

6
00:04:18,190 --> 00:04:19,520
(Yuming)

7
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:47,639
Hello?

8
00:04:48,279 --> 00:04:49,879
May I speak to Wen Yitong?

9
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,519
She's out leading a tour.

10
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,759
Try her cell.

11
00:04:53,439 --> 00:04:54,879
Okay.

12
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:55,639
Thank you.

13
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:03,280
(Jinbaolong Hardware)

14
00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:05,279
Excuse me.

15
00:05:05,439 --> 00:05:06,920
Which bags are sturdier?

16
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:07,639
The ones on top

17
00:05:07,639 --> 00:05:08,560
or the ones below?

18
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,519
The ones on top.

19
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,720
What's the difference?

20
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:11,720
They cost more.

21
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:12,319
Got it.

22
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,639
Five bags. 80 yuan.

23
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,000
So that's 160.

24
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:34,160
♪Rolling in cash♪

25
00:05:34,730 --> 00:05:36,120
♪Rolling in cash♪

26
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:38,560
♪Rolling in cash♪

27
00:05:39,370 --> 00:05:40,840
♪Rolling in cash♪

28
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,560
♪Rolling in cash♪

29
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:49,840
♪Rolling in cash♪

30
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,960
♪Rolling in cash♪

31
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,340
♪Rolling in cash♪

32
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,160
Great.

33
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,440
(Yu Ming)

34
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:30,440
(Block this user)

35
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,360
Sorry.

36
00:06:35,959 --> 00:06:37,079
The number you have dialed

37
00:06:37,079 --> 00:06:38,279
is currently unavailable.

38
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:40,560
Please dial again later.

39
00:06:56,399 --> 00:06:57,160
Manager Zhan.

40
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:57,800
Mr. Yu.

41
00:06:58,199 --> 00:06:59,000
I found a locksmith

42
00:06:59,000 --> 00:06:59,600
for you.

43
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,279
Hello.

44
00:07:00,279 --> 00:07:00,879
Come on in.

45
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:01,560
Come.

46
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:02,720
I got this.

47
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,879
I'll keep an eye on him.

48
00:07:04,319 --> 00:07:05,079
Sure, sure.

49
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:05,879
Just tagging along.

50
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:06,959
Bye.

51
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,120
Hey, I know you.

52
00:07:12,279 --> 00:07:13,199
I've collected trash from you.

53
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,360
That's no reason to kneel.

54
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,199
Force of habit.

55
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,160
Which lock?

56
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,120
Over here.

57
00:07:19,759 --> 00:07:20,120
Okay.

58
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:26,800
Sir, all set.

59
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:27,759
Enter code.

60
00:07:45,079 --> 00:07:45,639
You forgot to pay me.

61
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:03,480
Everything okay?

62
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:07,439
That means...?

63
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:08,639
Two updates.

64
00:08:09,279 --> 00:08:10,000
One is bad.

65
00:08:10,759 --> 00:08:11,199
The other...

66
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:12,279
Start with the good news.

67
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:13,879
is even worse.

68
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,399
Quit stalling. Just say it.

69
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,040
The wall is busted.

70
00:08:18,199 --> 00:08:18,920
What?

71
00:08:19,519 --> 00:08:20,240
Busted?

72
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:22,000
Wasn't it fine yesterday?

73
00:08:22,079 --> 00:08:23,000
What's worse?

74
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:24,480
The money's gone.

75
00:08:24,959 --> 00:08:25,480
Gone?

76
00:08:26,279 --> 00:08:27,000
Where'd it go?

77
00:08:31,439 --> 00:08:32,080
Buddy,

78
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:33,600
you have no idea.

79
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Someone died

80
00:08:35,519 --> 00:08:36,440
in this house.

81
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,200
Gum?

82
00:08:37,759 --> 00:08:38,519
You also owe

83
00:08:38,519 --> 00:08:39,559
120,000 yuan in property fees.

84
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:40,679
But listen,

85
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,000
in this house,

86
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:43,720
- Yu Ming.
- I found...

87
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,480
Here's the thing.

88
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,559
Someone died there.

89
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,279
Did the house shrink?

90
00:08:49,559 --> 00:08:50,600
Did the layout change?

91
00:08:53,679 --> 00:08:54,480
So you knew

92
00:08:54,639 --> 00:08:55,840
someone died there?

93
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,759
Of course I knew.

94
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:57,679
Why didn't you tell me?

95
00:08:57,799 --> 00:08:58,879
I thought we were friends!

96
00:08:58,879 --> 00:09:00,240
Since when are we friends?

97
00:09:00,279 --> 00:09:01,960
Yu Ming, this is business.

98
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,240
Business is business.

99
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:03,960
Buddy.

100
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:04,799
You must be kidding me

101
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:06,919
You played me!

102
00:09:06,919 --> 00:09:07,399
And those

103
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,320
120,000 in property fees

104
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,000
Pay them yourself.

105
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:09,960
Why should I pay them?

106
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,080
How are those

107
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:11,600
my property fees?

108
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,120
If you want that

109
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:12,759
120,000 yuan,

110
00:09:12,759 --> 00:09:13,799
go after the previous owner.

111
00:09:13,799 --> 00:09:14,639
They owed it, not me.

112
00:09:14,639 --> 00:09:15,440
The man hanged himself!

113
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,080
Who do I ask?

114
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,399
His wife...

115
00:09:18,039 --> 00:09:18,679
Well, she's in jail.

116
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,000
They have a daughter.

117
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:23,600
Her name is Chen Zinuo.

118
00:09:23,799 --> 00:09:24,559
I give you her number.

119
00:09:27,559 --> 00:09:28,919
(Chen Zinuo)
Go collect it from her.

120
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:29,230
(Chen Zinuo)

121
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:30,960
Hong Jinkui,

122
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,399
you've no idea what you just missed.

123
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,399
You deserve it.

124
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:35,840
From now on,

125
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,039
we're done.

126
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:37,799
We're done.

127
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,200
You're so gross.

128
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,200
So this house

129
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,679
has nothing to do with you now?

130
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,360
That's right.

131
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,240
So everything

132
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:48,080
inside this house—

133
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:48,840
none of it is yours?

134
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:49,440
- Right?
- Not a thing.

135
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,080
Put it in writing.

136
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:50,960
You dare?

137
00:09:51,039 --> 00:09:51,919
Sure.

138
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:52,879
Fine.

139
00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:54,399
You asked for it.

140
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,519
You just won't leave me alone,

141
00:10:09,519 --> 00:10:09,840
will you?

142
00:10:09,879 --> 00:10:10,360
How many times?

143
00:10:10,399 --> 00:10:10,960
Don't wait for me here!

144
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:19,279
You're completely insane.

145
00:10:26,039 --> 00:10:26,799
Have you lost your mind?

146
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:28,399
Why'd you borrow so much?

147
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:29,159
Didn't I tell you

148
00:10:29,159 --> 00:10:29,840
to avoid loan sharks?

149
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:30,519
Didn't I tell you?

150
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,159
I didn't borrow this money.

151
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,720
It came to me

152
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:35,159
on its own.

153
00:10:35,159 --> 00:10:36,279
How are you going to pay it back?

154
00:10:36,279 --> 00:10:38,200
I told you, I didn't borrow it.

155
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,679
Buying that house was the best decision.

156
00:10:39,759 --> 00:10:41,039
That villa...

157
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,080
it was waiting for me.

158
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,879
It was meant to be mine.

159
00:10:43,919 --> 00:10:44,759
- I was meant to own it.
- Listen to me.

160
00:10:44,879 --> 00:10:45,480
The loan sharks...

161
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:46,200
Do you know that villa...

162
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,759
You can't mess with them.

163
00:10:47,919 --> 00:10:49,039
You'll lose everything.

164
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:49,679
So much...

165
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:52,559
That villa is a goose

166
00:10:52,559 --> 00:10:54,200
that lays golden eggs.

167
00:10:55,639 --> 00:10:56,559
One after another.

168
00:10:56,559 --> 00:10:57,279
Hello? Can you connect me

169
00:10:57,279 --> 00:10:58,080
to Psychiatry?

170
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:58,639
Hang up.

171
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,279
I'm not making this up.

172
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:03,200
This money is heaven-sent.

173
00:11:03,279 --> 00:11:04,480
Luck is finally on our side.

174
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:05,440
It's finally

175
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,600
our turn.

176
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,960
We should be thrilled.

177
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:08,919
We should be excited.

178
00:11:08,919 --> 00:11:09,960
We should celebrate.

179
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:10,559
Kiss me!

180
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:11,799
You're insane.

181
00:11:11,799 --> 00:11:13,000
Yu Ming, you're out of your mind.

182
00:11:13,759 --> 00:11:15,039
Keep this up, and I'm calling the cops.

183
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,919
Relax...

184
00:11:17,919 --> 00:11:18,200
I...

185
00:11:55,919 --> 00:11:56,320
Name?

186
00:11:56,759 --> 00:11:57,440
Yu Ming.

187
00:11:58,879 --> 00:11:59,639
Y-E-U?

188
00:11:59,639 --> 00:12:00,799
No, not that Yeu.

189
00:12:00,799 --> 00:12:01,519
Y-U, Yu.

190
00:12:02,879 --> 00:12:04,360
We're legally married.

191
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,240
A real married couple.

192
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:07,519
We've had

193
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:08,240
some issues lately.

194
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,159
So I brought...

195
00:12:09,159 --> 00:12:10,120
When did you bring him in?

196
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:10,799
This afternoon.

197
00:12:10,919 --> 00:12:11,240
Where?

198
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:11,919
At an internet café.

199
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:13,679
Bigfoot?

200
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:14,720
Guo Li!

201
00:12:18,519 --> 00:12:19,279
What are you two doing here?

202
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:23,580
(Wanbei Police Station)

203
00:12:23,799 --> 00:12:24,960
Don't let this happen again,

204
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:25,320
okay?

205
00:12:25,399 --> 00:12:25,919
Yes, sir.

206
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:26,639
Thank you.

207
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,159
Thanks. Have a good one.

208
00:12:29,519 --> 00:12:30,120
I can't believe you.

209
00:12:34,799 --> 00:12:35,399
Give me the keys.

210
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:38,679
Do you know why

211
00:12:38,679 --> 00:12:39,519
Guo Li gave you a hat?

212
00:12:39,879 --> 00:12:41,519
Even your old friend
think you're embarrassing.

213
00:12:41,559 --> 00:12:42,799
She gave it to you
so you could hide your face.

214
00:13:10,159 --> 00:13:10,559
That...

215
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:11,679
Small world.

216
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:12,440
Yeah.

217
00:13:12,799 --> 00:13:13,440
Why are you still here?

218
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:13,960
I...

219
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:14,799
I just remembered

220
00:13:14,799 --> 00:13:16,440
something about a friend.

221
00:13:16,559 --> 00:13:17,480
I wanted to ask you.

222
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,080
He's a screenwriter.

223
00:13:19,159 --> 00:13:20,159
He's writing a script.

224
00:13:20,559 --> 00:13:21,320
Since when

225
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,080
you know screenwriters?

226
00:13:22,559 --> 00:13:23,360
Why have I never heard of him?

227
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,279
A new friend.

228
00:13:25,919 --> 00:13:26,519
A guy or a girl?

229
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:27,440
A guy.

230
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:28,480
Good-looking?

231
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,039
Looks like Guo Jingfei.

232
00:13:31,159 --> 00:13:31,519
Never mind, then.

233
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:32,960
Back to the point.

234
00:13:33,039 --> 00:13:34,440
In his script,

235
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,519
someone finds an antique

236
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,480
inside a house.

237
00:13:36,679 --> 00:13:38,120
Legally speaking,

238
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:38,960
does it belong to him?

239
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:40,879
Can he prove

240
00:13:40,879 --> 00:13:41,720
it's a family heirloom?

241
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:42,200
No.

242
00:13:44,279 --> 00:13:45,639
What if he's renting the house?

243
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:46,799
Ask the landlord.

244
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:48,679
Right.

245
00:13:49,159 --> 00:13:50,399
What if he owns the house?

246
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,320
He bought it himself,

247
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:51,840
and found an antique.

248
00:13:51,879 --> 00:13:53,039
Could it belong to him?

249
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,799
That depends on

250
00:13:54,799 --> 00:13:55,840
when

251
00:13:55,919 --> 00:13:57,000
and what kind of antique

252
00:13:57,039 --> 00:13:57,679
your writer friend invented.

253
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:01,080
He hasn't figured that out yet.

254
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:01,840
What are you asking?

255
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:02,200
No,

256
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,600
it's...

257
00:14:03,639 --> 00:14:04,720
He's a little confused too.

258
00:14:04,799 --> 00:14:06,039
Let's say it's not an antique.

259
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,000
Let's say it's gold.

260
00:14:07,159 --> 00:14:07,399
Right.

261
00:14:07,759 --> 00:14:09,120
You can spend it right away.

262
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:09,799
Nobody knew

263
00:14:09,879 --> 00:14:10,840
it was there.

264
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,440
Nobody was looking for it.

265
00:14:12,639 --> 00:14:13,519
Then he finds it.

266
00:14:13,639 --> 00:14:15,000
Can he keep the gold?

267
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,879
That's such a cliché.

268
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,200
Tell your friend to rewrite it.

269
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,840
He's stubborn. He won't listen.

270
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,240
No wonder

271
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:22,879
nobody watches TV anymore.

272
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,919
Tell your friend to find out first

273
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,200
whether the property has any heirs.

274
00:14:26,399 --> 00:14:27,559
He can look it up online.

275
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:28,960
If I remember correctly,

276
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,080
collective property stays collective.

277
00:14:30,159 --> 00:14:31,360
No heirs? It goes to the state.

278
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:34,000
Got it.

279
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,080
Why are you carrying

280
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:36,759
so much cash today?

281
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:42,440
To buy stock.

282
00:14:42,759 --> 00:14:43,519
Pearl powder again?

283
00:14:43,679 --> 00:14:44,240
Fridge magnets.

284
00:14:44,399 --> 00:14:45,480
200,000 worth of fridge magnets?

285
00:14:48,159 --> 00:14:49,440
This money...

286
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:54,480
Captain Guo.

287
00:14:54,919 --> 00:14:55,639
The paperwork's done.

288
00:14:58,039 --> 00:14:59,279
Keep an eye on that money.

289
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,440
Don't get scammed again.

290
00:15:11,559 --> 00:15:12,559
Do you sell flashlights?

291
00:15:13,559 --> 00:15:14,360
Bottom shelf.

292
00:15:21,639 --> 00:15:22,159
How much?

293
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:23,159
35 yuan.

294
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:32,759
I'll pay cash.

295
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:56,039
One bill.

296
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:56,879
Authentic.

297
00:16:01,759 --> 00:16:02,240
What?

298
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,480
I'll pay with my phone.

299
00:16:10,519 --> 00:16:12,120
Do you sell money counters?

300
00:16:12,919 --> 00:16:13,320
Sure.

301
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:14,399
I'll take one.

302
00:16:15,399 --> 00:16:15,919
