579
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:32,720
Loser.

580
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:33,680
That's 300,000!

581
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:34,519
Loser.

582
00:27:34,559 --> 00:27:35,839
You can't do anything right.

583
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:37,519
Can't you ever amount to anything?

584
00:27:38,039 --> 00:27:39,440
Are you trying to kill me?

585
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:42,400
Please stop.

586
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:43,160
Ma'am,

587
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:44,400
please calm down.

588
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:45,960
Wenwen's parents,

589
00:27:46,279 --> 00:27:46,680
um...

590
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:47,519
Wu Xiaoxuan's parents

591
00:27:47,559 --> 00:27:48,319
have arrived at school.

592
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:49,440
Could one of you

593
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:50,359
come with me to handle it?

594
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:51,440
I'll go.

595
00:27:55,839 --> 00:27:56,200
Let's go.

596
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:03,039
The injury is on her face.

597
00:28:03,359 --> 00:28:05,079
Wenwen is a girl.

598
00:28:05,359 --> 00:28:06,319
What if she feels insecure

599
00:28:06,319 --> 00:28:07,279
and other kids

600
00:28:07,319 --> 00:28:07,920
pick on her?

601
00:28:08,279 --> 00:28:08,920
Let me be clear,

602
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,599
kids her age

603
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:12,240
care most about their appearance.

604
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:13,279
What if she breaks down

605
00:28:13,359 --> 00:28:14,319
and needs therapy?

606
00:28:14,519 --> 00:28:15,519
And even needs medication?

607
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:17,519
And if that scar doesn't heal properly,

608
00:28:17,759 --> 00:28:19,519
this won't be over in a few days.

609
00:28:19,519 --> 00:28:20,960
That scar could stay with her

610
00:28:21,359 --> 00:28:22,839
for the rest of her life.

611
00:28:23,119 --> 00:28:24,440
Ma'am.

612
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:26,160
The kids fell down together.

613
00:28:26,160 --> 00:28:27,440
We don't even know who started it.

614
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:28,400
Just 'cause she's hurt worse,

615
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,279
doesn't make her right.

616
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:30,559
Let's be reasonable.

617
00:28:30,799 --> 00:28:32,279
My son was hurt too.

618
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:33,839
Oh, really?

619
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:35,599
Did he need stitches?

620
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:36,799
Was the wound deep?

621
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:38,160
Was he bleeding?

622
00:28:38,279 --> 00:28:39,599
Was there blood everywhere?

623
00:28:39,799 --> 00:28:40,480
Stop right there.

624
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:41,519
Let me tell you,

625
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:43,839
Wenwen is my precious granddaughter.

626
00:28:44,079 --> 00:28:45,119
If anything happens to her,

627
00:28:45,119 --> 00:28:46,240
I couldn't go on living.

628
00:28:46,519 --> 00:28:47,519
And if I die,

629
00:28:47,759 --> 00:28:48,920
none of you will have any peace.

630
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:49,920
I've seen plenty of people

631
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:50,920
like you.

632
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,519
The facts aren't even clear yet,

633
00:28:52,559 --> 00:28:53,680
and you're already taking

634
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:54,400
the moral high ground.

635
00:28:54,599 --> 00:28:55,880
Yes, I admit

636
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:57,039
Wenwen bled more,

637
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:58,039
so everyone will naturally

638
00:28:58,039 --> 00:28:58,839
take your side.

639
00:28:59,079 --> 00:28:59,680
Then we'll

640
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:00,319
get torn apart online.

641
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:01,480
People will expose us,

642
00:29:01,519 --> 00:29:02,119
where we work,

643
00:29:02,200 --> 00:29:03,319
and even our home address,

644
00:29:03,559 --> 00:29:05,119
and put us on public trial.

645
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:06,400
Isn't that what you want?

646
00:29:07,200 --> 00:29:08,960
Get off your high horse.

647
00:29:10,119 --> 00:29:11,039
Why are you insulting me?

648
00:29:11,079 --> 00:29:11,799
Who said I was talking about you?

649
00:29:11,799 --> 00:29:12,559
Did I insult you?

650
00:29:12,559 --> 00:29:13,039
Stop that.

651
00:29:13,079 --> 00:29:14,640
We're not here to fight.

652
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:15,839
The most important thing

653
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:16,720
is to find out

654
00:29:16,759 --> 00:29:18,000
how serious

655
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:18,599
Wenwen's injury is.

656
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:19,039
Right?

657
00:29:19,119 --> 00:29:20,480
No need for more tests.

658
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:21,519
It's obviously serious.

659
00:29:21,519 --> 00:29:22,200
Let me handle it.

660
00:29:22,359 --> 00:29:23,279
I'll take care of this,

661
00:29:23,359 --> 00:29:23,720
okay?

662
00:29:24,039 --> 00:29:25,359
No matter who got hurt

663
00:29:25,559 --> 00:29:26,559
or who was hurt worse,

664
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:27,480
lots of people were there.

665
00:29:27,599 --> 00:29:28,200
Someone must have seen

666
00:29:28,279 --> 00:29:29,240
what happened.

667
00:29:29,559 --> 00:29:30,519
Isn't the school responsible?

668
00:29:30,799 --> 00:29:31,160
It is.

669
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:32,839
What we need now

670
00:29:32,839 --> 00:29:34,039
is to get the facts straight.

671
00:29:34,160 --> 00:29:35,680
Whoever's responsible is responsible.

672
00:29:36,079 --> 00:29:36,480
Right?

673
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:38,079
We can work out a solution together.

674
00:29:38,559 --> 00:29:39,440
Arguing here

675
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:40,200
won't solve anything.

676
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:45,680
Wenwen and Xiaoxuan

677
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,279
were playing around here,

678
00:29:47,640 --> 00:29:50,000
and accidentally fell downstairs.

679
00:29:50,599 --> 00:29:51,559
I noticed when I walked by.

680
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:08,559
Sir, please let us handle that.

681
00:30:49,799 --> 00:30:50,640
All right, stop staring.

682
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:51,880
Go back to class.

683
00:30:52,119 --> 00:30:53,440
Everyone, back to class.

684
00:30:53,599 --> 00:30:54,559
How many times do I have to say it?

685
00:30:54,599 --> 00:30:55,920
Get back to class.

686
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:57,000
Nothing to see here.

687
00:30:57,119 --> 00:30:58,079
Back to class.

688
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:04,079
Yu Ming.

689
00:31:04,440 --> 00:31:04,759
Director.

690
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:05,920
Stop cleaning.

691
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:06,519
Director.

692
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:07,839
Stop, don't do this.

693
00:31:07,839 --> 00:31:08,319
Blood.

694
00:31:08,480 --> 00:31:08,799
It's gone.

695
00:31:08,799 --> 00:31:09,640
It's all Wenwen's blood.

696
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:10,319
Stop.

697
00:31:10,799 --> 00:31:11,319
Please.

698
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:12,000
Put it down.

699
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:13,440
Stop.

700
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:15,759
Don't do this, Yu Ming.

701
00:31:15,799 --> 00:31:16,640
Please stop.

702
00:31:17,759 --> 00:31:18,559
There's still some in the crack.

703
00:31:18,559 --> 00:31:19,200
I see it.

704
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:19,559
I'll get it.

705
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:20,119
Sit down and rest.

706
00:31:20,279 --> 00:31:20,680
Give me that.

707
00:31:24,039 --> 00:31:25,119
The doctor said she's young,

708
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:25,839
so she'll heal quickly.

709
00:31:25,920 --> 00:31:26,640
She'll be okay.

710
00:31:31,799 --> 00:31:32,599
Don't do this.

711
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:37,920
What are you talking about?

712
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:39,119
Home field, away field...

713
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:40,680
If I didn't tell you,

714
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:42,319
could you tell which was which?

715
00:31:43,119 --> 00:31:43,680
Fine, I have to go.

716
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:48,319
Can't you figure it out yourself?

717
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:55,200
Your daughter?

718
00:31:56,240 --> 00:31:57,000
Your son?

719
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:58,759
Well, isn't that something.

720
00:32:00,039 --> 00:32:00,960
The one guy who hit our car.

721
00:32:01,359 --> 00:32:01,920
That headlight...

722
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:04,920
How about this?

723
00:32:05,359 --> 00:32:06,559
That headlight costs 300,000.

724
00:32:07,039 --> 00:32:08,000
Let's call it even.

725
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:09,240
Your daughter's forehead

726
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:10,440
for my headlight.

727
00:32:11,039 --> 00:32:11,599
What did you say?

728
00:32:11,599 --> 00:32:12,319
What did you say?

729
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:14,920
Calm down.

730
00:32:25,599 --> 00:32:26,000
What?

731
00:32:26,839 --> 00:32:28,759
How about this?

732
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:31,920
I'll give you three million.

733
00:32:32,039 --> 00:32:32,400
For what?

734
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:35,519
For five stitches on your head.

735
00:32:36,119 --> 00:32:36,759
Just five stitches.

736
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:37,640
Deal?

737
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:38,079
No.

738
00:33:06,710 --> 00:33:09,000
(Emergency)

739
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:14,240
Do I look ridiculous

740
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:15,680
with this net?

741
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:17,799
You look good in anything.

742
00:33:17,799 --> 00:33:18,799
You're gorgeous.

743
00:33:19,119 --> 00:33:20,039
Don't believe me? Ask Grandma.

744
00:33:21,599 --> 00:33:22,279
You look lovely.

745
00:33:22,680 --> 00:33:23,319
Come on, sit still.

746
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:26,079
Careful with that arm.

747
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:26,680
Your left one.

748
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:27,559
Did it hurt

749
00:33:27,720 --> 00:33:28,799
when they stitched you up?

750
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:30,079
Why would it hurt?

751
00:33:30,079 --> 00:33:31,039
They gave me anaesthetic.

752
00:33:31,559 --> 00:33:32,119
Did you cry?

753
00:33:32,799 --> 00:33:34,359
Why would I cry? I had anaesthetic.

754
00:33:38,640 --> 00:33:39,200
Where's dad?

755
00:34:11,119 --> 00:34:17,840
♪Once king of Flower-Fruit Mountain♪

756
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:21,719
♪Now lost upon the endless road♪

757
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:26,199
♪I fought demons for my master♪

758
00:34:26,920 --> 00:34:29,559
♪Yet he failed to understand♪

759
00:34:30,039 --> 00:34:34,280
♪He mistook loyalty for ill intent♪

760
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:37,079
♪A master's word is law♪

761
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:41,960
♪What did I do wrong♪

762
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:47,360
♪What did I do wrong♪

763
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:48,280
That Monkey King

764
00:34:48,679 --> 00:34:51,039
always shows up when I'm lost.

765
00:34:51,639 --> 00:34:53,800
He walks past me singing.

766
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:55,760
And as I watch him,

767
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:59,119
my mind gradually settles.

768
00:35:03,920 --> 00:35:05,119
I don't want porridge.

769
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:06,440
Then what do you want?

770
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:07,280
Fried chicken.

771
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,079
No fried chicken.

772
00:35:08,239 --> 00:35:09,480
The doctor said no spicy food,

773
00:35:09,519 --> 00:35:10,719
no seafood, beef, or lamb.

774
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:11,760
But fried chicken is chicken.

775
00:35:11,920 --> 00:35:12,639
Absolutely not.

776
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:13,960
It's too greasy.

777
00:35:14,039 --> 00:35:14,599
It's too greasy.

778
00:35:15,079 --> 00:35:16,639
Get better,
and Grandma will buy you some.

779
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:17,559
Get better,
and Grandma will buy you some.

780
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:18,559
I know what she means.

781
00:35:19,159 --> 00:35:20,079
She knows what I mean.

782
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:22,440
Here...

783
00:35:22,599 --> 00:35:23,480
Mom, stop fussing.

784
00:35:23,519 --> 00:35:24,119
You should head home.

785
00:35:24,159 --> 00:35:25,000
I've made up the bed for you.

786
00:35:25,079 --> 00:35:25,880
Everything's ready.

787
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:26,480
Go home.

788
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:27,480
All right, I'm off.

789
00:35:27,599 --> 00:35:28,480
Bye, grandma.

790
00:35:28,679 --> 00:35:29,320
Bye.

791
00:35:30,159 --> 00:35:30,440
What?

792
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:31,920
Stop playing and finish your food.

793
00:35:36,159 --> 00:35:36,679
What's wrong?

794
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,039
Has she ever hit you?

795
00:35:40,159 --> 00:35:40,639
Who?

796
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:42,440
Who else? That old witch.

797
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:43,679
Has she laid a hand on you?

798
00:35:43,760 --> 00:35:44,639
I'll report her if she has.

799
00:35:44,679 --> 00:35:45,360
Report her for what?

800
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:46,079
She wouldn't dare.

801
00:35:48,480 --> 00:35:49,559
Now I need a new pair of glasses.

802
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:52,880
You were so protective of him today.

803
00:35:53,039 --> 00:35:54,599
What changed?

804
00:35:55,199 --> 00:35:56,039
Thought you were leaving him.

805
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,280
Divorce is one thing.

806
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,079
Stopping a fight is another.

807
00:35:58,119 --> 00:35:59,199
I couldn't just stand there

808
00:35:59,199 --> 00:36:00,119
and watch Sun Lanying beat him.

809
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:02,400
Don't worry about it. Go home.

810
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:03,159
Go get some rest.

811
00:36:03,199 --> 00:36:03,880
You've had a long day.

812
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:04,480
Go home and get some sleep.

813
00:36:05,239 --> 00:36:05,840
All right, I'm going.

814
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:06,880
Be careful. Watch for traffic.

815
00:36:08,280 --> 00:36:09,440
I'll buy you a new pair of glasses.

816
00:36:17,559 --> 00:36:18,000
Have you finished?

817
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:20,159
Such a fuss over porridge.

818
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:23,119
Tell me,

819
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:24,719
this afternoon,

820
00:36:25,679 --> 00:36:26,960
who pushed whom?

821
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:27,679
Who started it?

822
00:36:28,199 --> 00:36:29,400
Nobody did.

823
00:36:29,559 --> 00:36:30,800
Blame me for being skinny.

824
00:36:31,079 --> 00:36:32,239
I never get enough fried chicken.

825
00:36:32,400 --> 00:36:33,599
I'm as skinny as a monkey.

826
00:36:34,039 --> 00:36:35,199
No wonder I'm the one who got hurt.

827
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,119
Listen to you.

828
00:36:36,159 --> 00:36:36,840
But nice try.

829
00:36:39,039 --> 00:36:40,719
None of this is dad's fault.

830
00:36:41,599 --> 00:36:42,480
So you heard everything?

831
00:36:42,519 --> 00:36:43,639
You were so loud.

832
00:36:43,679 --> 00:36:44,639
How could I not?

833
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:46,119
That's why you can't get hurt.

834
00:36:46,119 --> 00:36:46,760
You know?

835
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:48,760
Whatever comes your way,

836
00:36:48,800 --> 00:36:50,159
you need to get through it.

837
00:36:50,199 --> 00:36:50,599
Keep going.

838
00:36:50,639 --> 00:36:51,239
Stay strong.

839
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:53,159
If you're strong, Dad will be too.

840
00:36:53,519 --> 00:36:54,239
If you're okay,

841
00:36:54,239 --> 00:36:55,119
Dad will be okay too.

842
00:36:55,159 --> 00:36:55,880
Got it?

843
00:36:58,840 --> 00:36:59,760
After your Dad and I get...

844
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:00,159
Dad!

845
00:37:07,239 --> 00:37:08,159
Thank you.

846
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:10,360
Even now,

847
00:37:11,079 --> 00:37:12,400
you're still standing up for me.

848
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:16,159
That's a another matter.

849
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:24,800
Wenwen is a good kid.

850
00:37:25,159 --> 00:37:25,800
So well-behaved.

851
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:27,239
Why...

852
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:28,960
does she have to go through this?

853
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:31,880
Why her?

854
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:33,800
Why not someone else?

855
00:37:39,480 --> 00:37:41,320
You seem distracted with Wenwen lately.

856
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:42,360
Do you know why?

857
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:46,519
I do.

858
00:37:48,239 --> 00:37:49,760
She's taking after your brother.

859
00:37:51,039 --> 00:37:51,599
When you look at her,

860
00:37:51,599 --> 00:37:52,880
it's like seeing him.

861
00:37:54,639 --> 00:37:55,920
You feel you owe your brother.

862
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:57,039
You owe Wenwen.

863
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:58,800
It's eating you up.

864
00:38:02,119 --> 00:38:03,079
I just want to ask,

865
00:38:03,679 --> 00:38:04,639
living like this...

866
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:06,920
when will it end?

867
00:38:11,239 --> 00:38:11,719
Yitong.

868
00:38:12,719 --> 00:38:13,599
Listen.

869
00:38:14,079 --> 00:38:14,840
Come back to the house with me.

870
00:38:14,840 --> 00:38:15,519
I must show you something.

871
00:38:15,519 --> 00:38:16,400
Don't mention that house.

872
00:38:17,559 --> 00:38:18,280
I know.

873
00:38:18,800 --> 00:38:20,440
My whole family has held you back.

874
00:38:21,159 --> 00:38:22,000
You've carried us for too long.

875
00:38:22,599 --> 00:38:23,960
But this time, trust me.

876
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:26,440
Better days are ahead.

877
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:28,559
Don't leave me.

878
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:30,400
Please.

879
00:42:56,440 --> 00:42:57,559
I've got a hammer!

880
00:42:57,559 --> 00:42:58,639
I'm not afraid of you!

881
00:42:58,679 --> 00:42:59,599
I'm not afraid!

882
00:43:05,080 --> 00:43:07,880
(Next Episode）

883
00:43:08,239 --> 00:43:09,559
(Guo Jingfei)
Hi, I'm Guo Jingfei.

884
00:43:09,559 --> 00:43:11,880
(Guo Jingfei)
I invite you to watch Wonder Wall.

885
00:43:14,599 --> 00:43:16,079
I just want to
check yesterday's footage.

886
00:43:16,280 --> 00:43:17,559
Those two knew this place

887
00:43:17,599 --> 00:43:18,400
really well.

888
00:43:18,480 --> 00:43:19,840
If they're familiar with this place,

889
00:43:19,840 --> 00:43:21,119
could they be someone you know?

890
00:43:21,760 --> 00:43:22,159
Perhaps you should go back

891
00:43:22,159 --> 00:43:23,039
to check

